newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures end up, commission house buying noted.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures end up, commission house buying noted.

text.p: FCOJ futures continued to climb higher on mostly commission house buying despite technical and fundamental signals that point to lower prices, dealers said.
Trade scale-up selling limited gains, they added.

Players await the weekly movement figures from the Florida Citrus Processors Association, released later today. Movement has been consistently weak while Florida is still expected to produce a record 220 million 90-lb boxes.
Technically, resistance was seen between present levels and 87.00 cents in the most-active May contract.
Firm support in May was seen the recent low of 77.50.
May ended up 1.30 cents at 83.80 cents per pound, traded 85.20 to 82.90. Spot March closed 1.35 higher at 81.15 cents.
Volume was estimated at 3,750 lots compared with Wednesday's official volume of 3,464 lots.
The last trading day for the spot month is March 10.
Warm weather in Florida's citrus belt is expected to continue through the weekend, forecasters said.
